RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 67. Maiden Claiming Purse 14500. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG BOY VICK pressed the pace in the four path, bid in early stretch, was clear and then lasted under mild urging. SEMINOLE AUSTIN raced in the five path and rallied belatedly for the place. SAN RONIN saved ground, bid inside, then lacked a late bid. HITCHPIN raced three wide, then bid belatedly five wide. STUDENT PRINCE pressed the pace in the three path, then faltered in the stretch. MOTION TO ADJOURN led inside, then couldn't last. REVS MEDAL saved ground to no avail. AMERIGOROUND raced well back.

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Jay J. Holden & Arven P. Holden

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BACK ON TRACK prompted the early pace, took command into the turn, opened a clear advantage turning for home and drew clear. RUNTOLIVE reserved while racing four wide down the backside, rallied through the turn from three wide and kept coming steadily to gain the place. BAYTOWN ANGEL stalked the pace from the fence to the turn, was set to an early drive while prominent turning for home and finished evenly. POP CHART settled in hand while tracking three wide, angled out at the head of the stretch and made a mild late gain down the lane. PRETTY VEGAS bobbled slightly at the start, sped up to the lead for the first quarter and faded. LADY YELLOWSTONE chased the leaders down the backside, was set to an early drive into the turn and lacked a response. GOGO BOBBYJO broke inward to brush rival leaving the gate, raced near the rear all the way and failed to menaced. MISTY OCEAN was never a threat.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 4 1M Dirt CR: 84. Claiming Purse 20000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since August 11 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claiming Races F or $7,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility And Allowances) Indiana Bred maiden and Indiana Bred claiming races for 15,000 or less not considered in eligibility.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: YAK stalked the pace from three wide to the backstretch, moved to the lead at the half mile pole, dueled with the runner-up through the turn and down the lane and prevailed at the wire in a determined drive. HE TAKES CHARGE tracked the pace through the first turn, made a four wide middle move to challenge for the lead leaving the half mile pole, battled with the winner to the wire in a good effort while failing to get by. KING SOCIAL tracked the leaders from two wide down the backstretch, rallied turning for home and made a mild non-threatening bid down the lane to garner the show. SHIPSHAPE pressed the pace through the first turn, briefly led down the backside, kept on to be prominent to the top of the lane and finished evenly. HIGH BROW unhurried early to be at the back in the first turn and steadily made up ground through the pack. GENERATOR never menaced racing evenly in mid-pack. FLYING SAMURAI broke a step slow to trail into the turn, chased down the backside, circled five wide coming home showing some late interest. BLAZEN ROAD flashed brief speed to lead in the first turn and came up empty. DEUTERONOMYSTRONG was never a threat.
